{
  "texts": [
    "The architecture of EDSR combines basic convolution layers with residual blocks and concludes with an upsampling layer, optimizing the model for efficient performance with lower time and space complexities.",
    "3.3.3.1 HRNet HRNet employs a 4-level hierarchical network, with interconnected networks at each level.",
    "The incorporation of distinct levels is purported to amplify information compared to conventional encoder-decoder models (Zhao et al. 2020c).",
    "Within each level, convolution operations are followed by residual dense blocks, subsequently succeeded by residual global blocks that utilize MLPs for attention computation, thereby enhancing contextual understanding.",
    "To facilitate inter-level fusion, pixelshuffling and pixelunshuffling techniques are employed."
  ]
}